<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRY POACHED FRESH PEARS IN FUDGE SAUCE; 
</P>
<P>
A PERFECT GRAND FINALE AT FESTIVE DINNER PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poached Pears With Fudge Sauce will make a grand finale at a festive dinner 
party. 
</P>
<P>
Fresh pears become a spectacular dessert when poached and topped with fudge 
sauce. The fruit is peeled and simmered in lemon flavored syrup, then cooled to 
room temperature or chilled. The remaining syrup is used to make the fudge 
sauce. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
POACHED PEARS WITH FUDGE SAUCE 
</P>
<P>
4 to 6 pears 
</P>
<P>
Lemon juice 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup sugar 
</P>
<P>
3 (1/2-inch) strips lemon peel 
</P>
<P>
1/2 vanilla bean, split lengthwise, optional 
</P>
<P>
2 cups water 
</P>
<P>
4 ounces semisweet chocolate 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons butter 
</P>
<P>
Peel pears, leaving stems intact. Rub pears with lemon juice immediately after 
peeling. Combine sugar, lemon peel, vanilla bean and water in large pan. Heat 
liquid to dissolve sugar. Add pears, cover and simmer 10 to 30 minutes or until 
tender. 
</P>
<P>
Remove pears from pan and cool. Remove vanilla bean and lemon peel from liquid. 
Continue to cook liquid until reduced to 1/3 cup and mixture thickens slightly. 
Add chocolate and heat until melted. Stir in butter until melted. 
</P>
<P>
Serve pears at room temperature or chilled, upright on serving plate with warm 
fudge sauce. Makes 4 to 6 servings. 
</P>
<P>
Note: Pears may be poached ahead and chilled. Fudge sauce may be prepared ahead 
and reheated in microwave oven. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, POACHED PEARS WITH FUDGE SAUCE 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
