<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Teachers Take Strike Vote Teachers at Adams Junior High School were 
among thousands of Los Angeles Unified School District teachers, counselors, 
nurses and librarians who cast ballots Wednesday to decide whether they should 
strike on May 30. Union President Wayne Johnson said he hopes that the results, 
to be announced Monday, will show at least 65% of the union's 22,000 members in 
favor of a walkout. More than 16,000 teachers voted March 7 to reject the 
district's last offer and authorize a strike, but a date was not specified. The 
district has offered teachers a 20% raise over three years; the union is 
pressing for a 21% increase over two years. Also at issue are proposals to give 
elementary teachers a paid preparation period and create school councils that 
would give teachers more authority on how schools are run. LARRY DAVIS / Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
