<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ACTOR TODD BRIDGES DENIED REDUCED BAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite a plea from actor Todd Bridges, a Superior Court judge refused to lower 
his $2-million bail on charges that he nearly killed a man in a shooting in a 
rock cocaine house in February. 
</P>
<P>
"What I can't understand is why I'm a danger to society," Bridges, 23, a former 
child star of the NBC-TV series "Diff'rent Strokes," told Judge David Horowitz. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges is charged with attempted murder in the shooting of a 25-year-old man 
who was allegedly serving as a lookout at a South-Central Los Angeles rock 
house Feb. 2. 
</P>
<P>
Horowitz turned down the defense request to lower Bridges' bail to $50,000 and 
ordered him to remain in custody pending a May 19 pretrial hearing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
