<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELECTRIC CARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When I was a little kid in Chicago, my friend Frank lived with his mother 
around the corner in a house with a garage, which housed a black electric 
sedan. It ran almost noiselessly, seated three, had a top speed of about 30, 
and a range of (let's say) 50 miles. In other words, it was absolutely perfect 
for city driving. When Frank's mother came home from shopping, visiting, or 
whatever, she recharged this marvelous contraption by plugging it into a garage 
socket. 
</P>
<P>
What's the catch, if any? 
</P>
<P>
LEON WOLFF 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
