<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER CHAMP TUBBS AND EVANS TO FIGHT AT STRAND TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former World Boxing Assn. heavyweight champion Tony Tubbs meets Mike Evans in a 
10-round fight tonight at the Strand in Redondo Beach. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first fight for Tubbs (25-2) since being knocked out in two rounds 
by Mike Tyson last March in Tokyo. Tubbs, 30, is ranked seventh by the World 
Boxing Council, while Evans (17-2) is 15th. 
</P>
<P>
Tubbs, 225 pounds, won the title from Greg Page on a 15-round unanimous 
decision on April 29, 1985, but lost a majority decision to Tim Witherspoon in 
his next bout nine months later. Evans is expected to fight at 250. 
</P>
<P>
The five-bout card, beginning at 7:30 p.m., includes three fights with South 
Bay boxers. Carson junior welterweight Hedgmon Robertson (25-4) will face Steve 
Lewis (14-5), Redondo Beach super middleweight Troy Emerson (6-2) opposes Tom 
Lillard in a four-round bout and Redondo Beach heavyweight Jimmy Ellis, a 
former football standout at Redondo High, faces Darren Etheridge. The other 
bout matches heavyweights Troy Baudoin and Tim Mixon in their pro debuts. 
STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</TEXT>
