EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Adolph Coors Co.: The brewing company announced a first-quarter net loss of 
$4.8 million, contrasted with net income of $3.7 million a year ago. Revenue, 
however, rose 12.9% to $324 million. Golden, Colo.-based Coors blamed the 
earnings decline on lower beer shipments and higher manufacturing costs. 
</P>
