<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: 'BIG' TAKES TOP SPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Big" is finally making the big splash it was expected to make a few weeks ago. 
After three weeks, the Tom Hanks comedy ascended to No. 1 on the Billboard 
magazine rental chart. "Stealing Home," featuring best-actress Oscar winner 
Jodie Foster, debuted at No. 25, but could wind up in the Top 10 -- thanks to 
the exposure from Foster's Oscar victory. "Hellbound: Hellraiser II," a 
favorite among horror fans -- especially the young ones -- debuted at No. 17. 
Look for this one to be the most popular horror rental of the next few weeks. 
"Mystic Pizza," the comedy/drama about three female friends who work at a pizza 
joint, entered the chart at No. 19 and has definite Top 10 potential. 
</P>
<P>
* An action movie featuring two big stars, Gene Hackman and Danny Glover, "Bat 
21" could be a rental smash. "Lethal Weapon" made Glover a big star in the 
rental market. Also, Hackman is hot now because of his best-actor nomination 
for "Mississippi Burning." 
</P>
