<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: WHITTIER; 
</P>
<P>
58-HOME DEVELOPMENT TO BE WALLED AND GATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Whittier City Council has approved construction of 58 homes on a parcel of 
vacant land on Painter Avenue north of Mulberry Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The developer wants to build a planned community surrounded by six-foot walls 
and having gated entrances and private streets, said Patrick Loy of Lewis Homes 
of California. House prices in the development, which will include 
single-family homes and duplexes, will start at about $240,000, Loy said. 
</P>
