<P>
ST. JOHN BOSCO HIGH GETS CAREER EDUCATION AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BELLFLOWER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. John Bosco High School has been named a recipient of a $100 presidential 
award and plaque from the California Career Education Assn. for expansion of 
its exemplary program in career education, according to Brother Frank Bracchi, 
the school's career technician. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
