</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Navy frigate Trippe and the oiler Platte collided in the Atlantic on 
Wednesday, leaving a 25-foot gash in the Platte. The vessels were taking part 
in the same exercise as the battleship Iowa, the Navy reported. 
</P>
<P>
"There was one minor injury. A crew member got his knee bruised," a Navy 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The Platte and Trippe were participating in the same Atlantic Fleet exercise, 
Fleetex 3-89, as the battleship Iowa, on which at least 47 sailors were killed 
in an explosion and fire in a gun turret. 
</P>
<P>
The Platte and Trippe were not in the same operating area, a spokesman said. 
The frigate and oiler were 500 miles east of Jacksonville, Fla., while the Iowa 
was 330 miles northeast of Puerto Rico. 
</P>
<P>
The Navy was investigating the cause of the collision. 
