<HEADLINE>
<P>
UTAH GOVERNOR SIGNS BILL TO PROVIDE FUSION FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SALT LAKE CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Utah Gov. Norman H. Bangerter Wednesday signed legislation setting aside $5 
million to develop the room-temperature nuclear fusion process being called a 
possible source of cheap, safe energy. 
</P>
<P>
Bangerter said work needs to continue as quickly as possible to develop the 
technology and explore commercial application. 
</P>
<P>
Scientists nationwide have been attempting to duplicate the claimed fusion 
breakthrough at the University of Utah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
