<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALKER DEFENDS HIS MOBIL INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish to respond to those publicly opposing my petition drive to qualify an 
initiative to prohibit the storage of large quantities of hydrofluoric acid at 
the Mobil Oil refinery in Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
Everyone, with the exception of the Mobil Oil Corp., who has studied the issue 
agrees that hydrofluoric acid is an extremely lethal chemical that could, in 
the case of an accidental spill, threaten the lives of tens of thousands of 
Torrance residents. 
</P>
<P>
Everyone, with the exception of the Mobil Oil Corp., who has studied the issue 
agrees that the Mobil refinery has one of the worst safety records in Southern 
California. 
</P>
<P>
To prevent a catastrophic accident from happening here in Torrance, we must 
eliminate the threat. 
</P>
<P>
That is why I have been working the past eight months on a ballot initiative 
which prohibits the storage of large quantities of hydrofluoric acid. And that 
is why I and my City Council colleagues filed a lawsuit last week against Mobil 
Oil Corp. which asks for a permanent injunction against the use of hydrofluoric 
acid and other, less dangerous chemicals within the city of Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
But to defeat the mighty Mobil Goliath, this cannot be a battle between one 
councilman and Mobil, or seven council members and Mobil. Torrance residents 
must be brought into the battle. 
</P>
<P>
Only by allowing Torrance voters to speak out at the ballot box will Mobil -- 
and their high-priced lawyers -- truly understand that Torrance residents 
demand action now. 
</P>
<P>
The issue is not politics, or the perceived political ambitions of myself. The 
issue is nothing less than the health and safety of you and your family. 
</P>
<P>
If you have not yet done so, please sign your initiative petition and mail it 
to me today. 
</P>
<P>
DAN WALKER 
</P>
<P>
Member, Torrance City Council 
</P>
</TEXT>
