<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIRE KILLS 2 MEN IN SEPULVEDA APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men died after a fire broke out in a Sepulveda apartment Wednesday night, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The men -- one 41 and the other 50 -- were in the same apartment unit in the 
15100 block of Parthenia Street when the fire occurred about 8:50 p.m., said 
Los Angeles Fire Department spokesman Greg Acevedo. Their bodies were 
discovered after the fire was put out, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The victims' identities were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
The flames in the ground-floor unit were put out in about 10 minutes, 
authorities said. Damage was estimated at $26,000. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire was being investigated, Acevedo said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
