<TEXT>
<P>
One week before the Supreme Court hears arguments in a key abortion rights 
case, an abortion rights group took to the airwaves with a $2-million ad 
campaign while an anti-abortion group said it plans to run newspaper ads next 
week to stir America's grass roots. The National Abortion Rights Action League 
began running television, radio and newspaper ads to present its side and build 
on the energy displayed at an abortion rights march that drew at least 300,000 
to the nation's Capitol earlier this month. Meanwhile, the American Civil 
Liberties Union today plans to deliver more than 200,000 letters to the Justice 
Department asking the department to drop its attempt to persuade the Supreme 
Court to overturn the landmark 1973 decision legalizing abortion. Oral 
arguments are scheduled for next Wednesday. 
