<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Georgia Tech linebacker Kevin Salisbury was indicted on charges of aggravated 
battery and obstruction of justice in a January brawl at a restaurant in which 
a female student suffered a broken nose. 
</P>
<P>
Lewis Slaton, Fulton County district attorney, said that Salisbury, 21, and the 
victim, Lisa Steffee, 26, were involved in an a verbal confrontation at the 
restaurant Jan. 18 after "repeated profanity" by Salisbury and his companions. 
Slaton said a beer was thrown on one of Salisbury's friends, and the reserve 
linebacker struck Steffee with his fists. 
</P>
