<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Off-road racer Steve Centurioni, 40, of Pasadena was killed when his buggy 
crashed and burned during practice for Saturday's Mint 400 off-road race. Peter 
Kujundzick, a passenger, managed to escape after the vehicle flipped several 
times and burst into flames in the desert northeast of Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
Bureau of Land Management rangers and other drivers reported that Centurioni's 
buggy going at an excessive speed when it went out of control and flipped. A 
30-m.p.h. speed limit was in effect for practice. 
</P>
