<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: MALIBU; 
</P>
<P>
GROUP SUES L.A. COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Friends of the Santa Monica Mountains are suing Los Angeles County over the 
development of 150 single-family homes at the site of the former Renaissance 
Pleasure Faire in Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
The suit, similar to one filed this month by the Sierra Club and the Las 
Virgenes Homeowners Foundation, seeks to reverse a March ruling by the Los 
Angeles County Board of Supervisors that would allow development of the 
320-acre tract north of the Paramount Ranch land that is part of the Santa 
Monica Mountains National Recreation Area. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuits argue that the ruling did not take into account problems of 
drainage, traffic and the destruction of the view from the recreation area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
