<P>
BEVERLY HILLS SCHOOLS RECEIVE STATE AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beverly Hills Unified School District's four elementary schools have been named 
1988-89 California Distinguished Schools, the state's highest public award to 
recognize educational excellence. 
</P>
<P>
The schools, among the 233 winners announced recently by state Supt. William 
Honig, were selected on the basis of rank or improvement on the California 
Assessment Program tests for the third, sixth and eighth grades. 
</P>
<P>
The schools -- Beverly Vista, El Rodeo, Hawthorne and Horace Mann -- received 
the award for top performance in all categories. 
</P>
