<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
3-MONTH TERM FOR VIOLATING GUN BAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An alleged gang member who was the first person convicted of violating the 
city's new assault rifle ban was sentenced today to three months in prison. 
</P>
<P>
Carlton Diggs, 20, of Rancho Cucamonga was originally arrested in connection 
with a robbery in the Fairfax District on April 12. A miltary-style M-1 carbine 
and three loaded 30-round banana clips for the weapon were found in the bed of 
Diggs' pickup truck, City Atty. James K. Hahn said. The three-month term was 
added to a separate three-month sentence Diggs was given for violating parole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
