NATION; 
</P>
<P>
PUPPY'S 911 GROWL JUST IN FUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LINCOLN, Neb. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A dispatcher taking an emergency 911 call was puzzled when the caller said 
nothing, just growled. 
</P>
<P>
Dispatchers traced the call to a house, and when police arrived, they didn't 
find Spuds McKenzie, only a snarling 2-year-old pit bull named Sheba and two 
puppies, Lt. Lyle Roberts said. One of the puppies had the receiver of the 
push-button telephone in its mouth. 
</P>
<P>
"There were no humans in the house," Roberts said. 
</P>
