<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ADRIAN WHITE CHARGED IN BAR INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE PARK, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York Giants safety Adrian White has been arrested and charged with smashing 
a glass into a woman's face during an argument at a local lounge. 
</P>
<P>
White, a former University of Florida star who has been working with area 
children in anti-drug programs, was arrested Wednesday on a charge of 
aggravated battery and later released on his own recognizance from Clay County 
Jail. He is charged with shoving a drinking glass into the face of Kannika 
Corder, 34, during an argument early Wednesday at Limericks Lounge, said Police 
Lt. James Boivin. 
</P>
<P>
"It broke and cut her from her right eye to her right ear," said Boivin. She 
was listed in serious condition today at Humana Hospital in Orange Park. 
</P>
<P>
White, 25, also cut his hand and had to have eight stitches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
